<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>fairy lantern • magic lantern</xh5><p> <i>fairy lantern—</i>any of various plants of the genus <i>Calochortus:</i> The <u>fairy lantern</u> is similar to orchids, and quite a few orchids depend on fungi as much as they do on photosynthesis for their energy.</p><p> <div class="note">Note</div> The expression does not correlate in meaning with the phrase <b>fairy lamp</b>—a candle-burning night light usually of colored glass: In the Amusement Compound they light a horseshoe of <u>fairy-lamps</u> above the Jack and Jill.</p><p><i>magic lantern—</i>apparatus for throwing a magnified image of a picture, etc. on to a white screen: Usually some newly arrived acquisition occupied the center of the room—a <u>magic lantern</u>, a kaleidoscope or a game of puff-billiards.</p> </entry>
